article.description: Evan Fisher registered 18 points as Siena narrowly beat Manhattan 51-49 on Friday night.
article.headline: Fisher scores 18 to lift Siena over Manhattan 51-49
article.linkText: Fisher scores 18 to lift Siena over Manhattan 51-49
article.story: RIVERDALE, N.Y. -- Evan Fisher registered 18 points as Siena narrowly beat Manhattan 51-49 on Friday night. Jalen Pickett made two free throws with 10 seconds left for a 51-47 lead. Nehemiah Mack scored for Manhattan with four seconds left. Pickett was fouled again and missed the front end of a one-and-one with 3.9 seconds left, but Mack's half-court heave hit the backboard. Kadeem Smithen had nine rebounds for Siena (12-12, 7-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Tyler Reynolds had 18 points and nine rebounds for the Jaspers (7-17, 5-7). Ebube Ebube added seven rebounds. The Saints improve to 2-0 against the Jaspers on the season. Siena defeated Manhattan 53-40 on Jan. 26. Siena plays Rider on the road on Sunday. Manhattan matches up against Niagara on the road next Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
